{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/react-headroom/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"e4d1b4ba-b7cf-5a63-a899-d46995ad3016","html":"<p>It was so easy to get a professional looking navbar with just 3 lines of code.  This package seriously is so usable on mobile it is rediculous.  I found this package from <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/blog/100days/react-component/?utm_campaign=100%20Days%20of%20Gatsby&#x26;utm_source=hs_email&#x26;utm_medium=email&#x26;utm_content=82376619&#x26;_hsenc=p2ANqtz-_DBh1A1A-GEy2TujddXq_H1de5wGZ_X6jIqB2wv_PE7QgUk40pfi64jbSVHv-S3bfzKZOQywtoTuup2aeO0o_KpeiF8w&#x26;_hsmi=82376619\">day 4</a> of the 100 days of gatsby challenge.  It is by the wonderful man who brought us gatsbyjs Kyle Mathews, so you know its gotta be good.</p>\n<h2>install react-headroom</h2>\n<p>installation is easy</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">npm</span> i react-headroom</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Import Headroom</h2>\n<p>There was no instructions for es6 style imports that are common with gatsbyjs sites like mine, but it was intuitive to figure out.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Headroom <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react-headroom'</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Using Headroom</h2>\n<p>Simply wrap your existing content, Nav in my case, with the <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Headroom /&gt;</code> component and your off to the races.  The content will pop back into view when you scroll past then back up.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>Headroom</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n   <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>--</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">Your</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">content</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">goes</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">here</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">--</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>Headroom</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>See it in action</h2>\n<p>I think this simple package completely changes the ux of your site on mobile.  You can get that sticky nav out of the way, but its still right there with just a little bit of a scroll up.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.waylonwalker.com/react-headroom-b.gif\" alt=\"showing it in action on waylonwalker.com\"></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Here it is on <a href=\"waylonwalker.com\">waylonwalker.com</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Configurable</h2>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">react-headroom</code> is configurable, but I did not find it necessary.  I really like the simplicity that it brought by just adding the <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Headroom\\&gt;</code> component.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.waylonwalker.com/react-headroom-docs.png\" alt=\"react-headroom docs\"></p>\n<h2>Links</h2>\n<p>Check out the relavant links for more details.</p>\n<p><strong>GitHub</strong>: <a href=\"https://github.com/KyleAMathews/react-headroom\">https://github.com/KyleAMathews/react-headroom</a>\n<strong>Demo Site</strong>: <a href=\"https://kyleamathews.github.io/react-headroom/\">https://kyleamathews.github.io/react-headroom/</a>\n<strong>Docs</strong>: <a href=\"https://kyleamathews.github.io/react-headroom/\">https://kyleamathews.github.io/react-headroom/</a></p>","frontmatter":{"date":"2020-02-11T12:57:00.000Z","devto_url":null,"devto_id":null,"title":"I just added react-headroom to my site","description":"It was so easy to get a professional looking navbar with just 3 lines of code.  This thing is so usable on mobile.","path":"react-headroom","twitter_cover":{"id":"9dc83e53-4eb1-52be-b750-34f8b731529d","absolutePath":"/mnt/c/personal/ww/waylonwalkerv2/static/react-headroom.png","childImageSharp":{"id":"65803ac1-38c1-5968-8c0c-782ec6c49155","fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":800,"height":418,"src":"/static/429c9d6017acee6f3a08bce78850debe/267c5/react-headroom.png","srcSet":"/static/429c9d6017acee6f3a08bce78850debe/267c5/react-headroom.png 1x"}}},"cover":{"id":"9dc83e53-4eb1-52be-b750-34f8b731529d","absolutePath":"/mnt/c/personal/ww/waylonwalkerv2/static/react-headroom.png","childImageSharp":{"id":"65803ac1-38c1-5968-8c0c-782ec6c49155","fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":1000,"height":420,"src":"/static/429c9d6017acee6f3a08bce78850debe/a8734/react-headroom.png","srcSet":"/static/429c9d6017acee6f3a08bce78850debe/a8734/react-headroom.png 1x"},"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":2.380952380952381,"src":"/static/429c9d6017acee6f3a08bce78850debe/a8734/react-headroom.png","srcSet":"/static/429c9d6017acee6f3a08bce78850debe/2d6f8/react-headroom.png 250w,\n/static/429c9d6017acee6f3a08bce78850debe/03ac3/react-headroom.png 500w,\n/static/429c9d6017acee6f3a08bce78850debe/a8734/react-headroom.png 1000w","sizes":"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"id":"e4d1b4ba-b7cf-5a63-a899-d46995ad3016"}}}